$interpreted: Yamitsuki: Stop right there!
Izumi: A feather tribe?
Yamitsuki: ... No longer breathing...
Nigel: Yamitsuki! What is going on?
Yamitsuki: I heard some noises. I thought it was monsters.
Yamitsuki: I came in only to find this person killing someone else. I tried to interfere, but I was still a step too late...

Nigel: You two are both demihumans...
You're supposed to be comrades. Why...
Izumi: This Pero girl was infected by a monster and was trying to attack me. I was just acting out of self-defense.
Izumi: Sis here only saw the latter half. She made a mistake. I'm innocent.
Nigel: ... Yamitsuki, is that true?
Yamitsuki: ... It was true I only saw the end of it... However, I don't feel——

Nigel: Enough, if you wronged someone, you should own up to it. Plenty of demihumans have sacrificed already. 
The last thing we need is more killing between our own people.
Yamitsuki: Wait, Nigel!
Nigel: I apologize to you in place of Yamitsuki.
Nigel: However, what is your purpose of coming to Atlas?
Izumi: I heard rumors that the Kingdom of the Sun capitol crashed down around this area. So, I decided to come here to check it out~

Nigel: Check it out? What do you think this place is, some kind of tourist destination!
Do you realize how dangerous it is?
Izumi: This is my life we're talking about. Why do you have to be so mad about it?

Nigel: You bastard...
Do you have any idea how many demihumans wanted to live yet simply couldn't!?
Yamitsuki: Nigel, calm down.
Nigel: ... The abandoned capitol is currently occupied by a giant monster. If you want to throw your life away that badly, go ahead. Nobody's stopping you.
Nigel: Yamitsuki, let's go.
Nigel: ... One more thing. After we get back, find someone to come here and help. We can't leave her lying there all alone in this cold.
Yamitsuki: ...... I know.
